text: Aframonius is a genus of adapiform primate that lived in Africa during the late Eocene or early Oligocene. Fossils of the genus were found in the Jebel Qatrani Formation of Egypt. == References == === Bibliography === * Category:Prehistoric strepsirrhines Category:Prehistoric primate genera †Aframonium Category:Eocene primates Category:Eocene mammals of Africa Category:Fossils of Egypt Category:Fossil taxa described in 1995
